Spark_Session_Configuration

Apache Spark is highly configurable system,
Spark allows you to set those configuration using four different methods.

Configuration Spark Session :
	- Environment Variable
	- SPAR_HOME\conf\spark_defaults.conf
	- spark_submit command-line 
	- SparkConf object

Environment variable

  • SPAR_HOME\conf\spark_defaults.conf

  • SparkConf object
  • spark_submit command-line options

    SparkConf -- is for coding configuration in application it self
spark = SparkSession.builder \
		 .appName("SparkConf") \
		 .master("local[3]") \
		 .getOrCreate()

appName and Master is the SparkConf. We can config as we need as much we want.
but we should be aware for actual name.

	from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
	from pyspark import SparkConf

	if __name__ == '__main__':
		conf = SparkConf()
		conf.set('spark.app.name','SparkConf')
		conf.set('spark.master','local[3]')

from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark import SparkConf

if __name__ == "__main__":
	conf = SparkConf()
	conf.set('spark.app.name','SparkConf')
	conf.set('spark.master','local[3]')
	spark = SparkSession.builder \
			.config(conf=conf) \
			.getOrCreate()
	spark.stop()

Spark properties -- can be grouped in to categories

How to decide the

Spark Submit -- ``` ~ go to spark-submit help specially name flags such as --master --driver-memory --num-executor etc. will be used by Spark-Submit ``` Other all are `Spark Conf` object

Let say we have 

conf = SparkConf()
	conf.set('spark.app.name','SparkConf')
	conf.set('spark.master','local[3]')

we are not confirm for this are we using YARN cluster or kubernative.
If we encounter with issue we need to check in local so converting spark.master will be in application lever cause issue.
This all thing is hard coded so which isnt production based.

How to handle this ?

  • We can make this config to Properties file.
[SPARK_APP_CONFIGS]
- spark.app.name = Hello Spark
- spark.master = local[3]

Created key value pair in spark.conf file

After that creating ‘utils.py’ class

import configparser
from pyspark import SparkConfig()

def get_spark_app_config():
	spark_conf = SparkConfig()
	config = config.ConfigParser().read("spark.conf")

	for key,value in config.items("SPARK_APP_CONFIGS"): 
		spark_conf.set(key,value)

	return spark_conf

once it created then call this method in main class Spark_Main.py.

import os 
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from lib.logger import Log4J
from lib.utils import get_spark_app_config

if __name__ == '__main__':
	log4j_config_file = 'log4j.properties'
	os.environ["log4j.configurationFile"]= "file:" + log4j_config_file

	conf = get_spark_app_config()
	spark = SparkSession.builder \
			.config(conf=conf)
			.getOrCreate()
	logger = Log4J(spark)

	logger.info("Starting HelloSpark")
	
	spark.stop()

 
conf = get_spark_app_config()

here we fixed the hard coding issue. for log4j code Spark_log4jconfig

for reading all spark config spark.config -- SparkSession.sparkContext.getConf() method
